1
00:00:01,041 --> 00:00:03,583
Showering happened
every three to four days

2
00:00:04,833 --> 00:00:06,541
There was no shampoo, only soap

3
00:00:07,291 --> 00:00:09,833
And no scrubber or towel

4
00:00:11,041 --> 00:00:13,125
Whoever showered

5
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:16,666
Finished and put on his clothes
in the bathroom while still wet

6
00:00:16,708 --> 00:00:18,125
He put on his
clothes and went out

7
00:00:19,833 --> 00:00:23,041
The bathrooms were for anyone
who needed to relieve himself and so on

8
00:00:24,500 --> 00:00:25,958
Very few things

9
00:00:26,416 --> 00:00:29,166
Because someone sat
next to the bathroom door

10
00:00:29,166 --> 00:00:31,791
So the foul smell reached them

11
00:00:31,833 --> 00:00:34,708
The smell reached the
last room, the third room

12
00:00:35,250 --> 00:00:38,583
So only a few went
to the bathroom

13
00:00:39,833 --> 00:00:42,041
Interviewer: Did you
take turns cleaning it?

14
00:00:42,083 --> 00:00:43,416
Yes we cleaned it

15
00:00:44,416 --> 00:00:46,250
Interviewer: Did that
lessen the odor in the place?

16
00:00:47,708 --> 00:00:49,083
No, it made no difference

17
00:00:53,083 --> 00:00:55,875
Interviewer: Were you harassed
by the prisoners who were with you

18
00:00:55,875 --> 00:00:57,458
When you used the toilet?

19
00:00:59,083 --> 00:00:59,875
Yes

20
00:01:00,541 --> 00:01:04,291
Interviewer: What happened?
What did they bother you about?

21
00:01:06,166 --> 00:01:09,208
I wanted to shower

22
00:01:09,833 --> 00:01:13,583
And one prisoner was inside

23
00:01:15,708 --> 00:01:17,583
He said, Why do
you shower daily?

24
00:01:17,625 --> 00:01:20,041
And the water splashes onto us

25
00:01:20,041 --> 00:01:22,458
We sleep here at the
door and you don't care

26
00:01:22,500 --> 00:01:25,000
You sit at the other end

27
00:01:25,791 --> 00:01:27,208
He kept talking

28
00:01:27,375 --> 00:01:28,625
So I didn’t speak
then, I remained silent

29
00:01:29,125 --> 00:01:30,791
To avoid trouble

30
00:01:31,500 --> 00:01:33,750
Otherwise they’d take
us out and beat us outside

31
00:01:34,333 --> 00:01:37,833
So I stayed silent and didn’t speak, and he kept
talking alone until he’d finished and then he fell silent

32
00:01:41,666 --> 00:01:43,666
Interviewer: Some
of the people we met

33
00:01:43,666 --> 00:01:46,250
Said they would
go to the washrooms

34
00:01:46,625 --> 00:01:49,125
They’d use the toilet
or go to the showers

35
00:01:49,416 --> 00:01:52,041
Just to get some
time to themselves

36
00:01:52,416 --> 00:01:55,166
Away from the prison
atmosphere and the other prisoners

37
00:01:55,166 --> 00:01:58,291
Away from the atmosphere of fear

38
00:01:58,625 --> 00:02:03,041
So did you do that to feel
some privacy with yourself?

39
00:02:03,750 --> 00:02:07,916
Nothing like that, at the
end of the day it’s a prison

40
00:02:08,958 --> 00:02:13,875
Even if someone goes into
the bathroom, he’s still in prison

41
00:02:15,333 --> 00:02:17,083
That bathroom is
in the prison

42
00:02:17,833 --> 00:02:22,125
A person doesn’t leave the
cell and go somewhere else

43
00:02:22,541 --> 00:02:23,750
It’s in the same cell
